  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0dbd\u0dd3\u0da7\u0dbb\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db4\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dbd\u0dca 200 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0da9\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dd4\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A liter of fuel can be reduced by 200 rupees",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Janaka Ratnayake, chairman of the Public Utilities Commission, said today (7) that it is possible to provide a liter of fuel to the people at a price 200 rupees lower than the current price and the actual import cost of a liter of fuel is not more than 300 rupees.",
        "Mr. Ratnayake mentions that the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation has replaced the fuel import cost in the fuel price formula and by showing this price, the amount given to the petrol stations is also calculated to be higher.",
        "Mr. Rathnayake said that if the petroleum corporation has bought crude oil at $72.50 per barrel, even if it is $200 in the world market, Mr. Ratnayake said that a barrel of gasoline costs $171 and also mentioned that octane 92 gasoline has been imported at $100.",
        "Mr. Ratnayake said that octane 95 petrol was imported at 103 dollars, auto diesel at 112 dollars, super diesel at 115 dollars and kerosene at 105 dollars and the fuel price should be calculated according to the imported value.",
        "In this calculation, Mr. Rathnayake said that the oil corporation will get 200 rupees after losing the tax income, and in the end there will be no money to buy fuel.",
        "Chairman of the Public Utilities Commission Mr. Janaka Ratnayake said this while holding a special press conference."
      ],
